## Flow Captured

1. **Load demo root** (`https://michaelwegter.com/demos/solo-law/`)
   - B&W editorial hero image (grayscale filter applied)
   - Practice areas grid (Corporate, Litigation, IP, Regulatory)
   - Recent publications teaser
   - Navbar with firm name + language selector + CMS Login link

2. **Locale switch EN → ES**
   - Click ES button in navbar
   - UI chrome changes: "ÁREAS DE PRÁCTICA / PUBLICACIONES / CONTACTO"
   - Hero layout remains consistent, content text in Spanish

3. **CMS login (client-side SPA navigation)**
   - Click "EDITOR LOGIN" link
   - Navigate to `/cms/login` view (no page reload; Angular routing)
   - Form visible with email/password inputs

4. **Credential submission**
   - Pre-filled: `editor@solo-law.demo` / `Demo2026!`
   - Submit button clicked
   - Navigates to `/cms/dashboard` (async JWT auth, backend returns token)

5. **CMS dashboard view**
   - Sidebar nav visible (Dashboard selected)
   - Stat cards rendered: "4 PRACTICE AREAS / 5 PUBLICATIONS / 3 LANGUAGES / 0 BRAND ASSETS"
   - Color-coded sidebar with icons (Professional, institutional style)

---

## Quality Notes

- **Images:** All 4 screenshots are valid 1280×720 PNG, no corruption, crisp text rendering
- **Video:** WebM format, ~30s duration covering the complete hero-to-dashboard flow, smooth transitions
- **No WebGPU AI panel capture:** Headless Playwright has no GPU, so AI Assist panel shows placeholder text ("Open any Practice Area..."). This is documented in deploy-test.out as W2. Acceptable for proposal media — the CMS interface is the primary focus, and the static panels are sufficient to show the design system
- **Locale switching confirmed:** Both EN and ES screenshots verify i18n is wired and responsive
- **Responsive design:** Screenshots at 1280×720 (desktop viewport) match the demo's target audience (law firm website)

---

## handoff
- produced: 4 desktop hero+CMS screenshots (PNG 1280×720), 1 deterministic hero-flow video (WebM ~30s); all assets in `media-captures/` subdirectory
- decisions: video captures EN→ES locale switch + CMS login flow (the core differentiator); WebGPU AI panel unavailable in headless but acceptable (static UI shown); screenshots at desktop 1280×720 (appropriate for law firm audience)
- next needs: proposal-writer step embeds screenshot URLs and video link in cover letter, one-pager, and PPTX deck; link format `./demos/solo-law/` for internal references, absolute https://michaelwegter.com/demos/solo-law/ for external references
- risks: none — all media assets valid, flow is deterministic and repeatable; demo is live and passing deploy-test
